<subSubSection pageNumber="529" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="529">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Note:</emphasis>
Blake (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Rhodora</emphasis>
20: 67. 1918) chose 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Clayton 91</emphasis>
(BM) as 
<typeStatus pageNumber="529">lectotype</typeStatus>
, a specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) Pennell" authorityName="Pennell" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Orobanchaceae" genus="Aureolaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageNumber="529" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="virginica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Aureolaria virginica</emphasis>
(L.) Pennell
</taxonomicName>
, into the synonymy of which this name would therefore fall. However, usage follows Pennell (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Rhodora</emphasis>
20: 133. 1918), who argued that the Kalm specimen (764.6 LINN) fitted 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Linnaeusâ€™" pageNumber="529">Linnaeus'</normalizedToken>
diagnosis better and should therefore be the type. It is identifiable as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Farw." baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Orobanchaceae" genus="Aureolaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageNumber="529" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flava">A. flava</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Reveal (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Taxon</emphasis>
41: 143. 1992) therefore proposed the conservation of the name with the Kalm sheet as conserved type. However, the Committee for Spermatophyta (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Taxon</emphasis>
43: 274. 1994) did not recommend acceptance, arguing that it was unnecessary as Pennell (1913), despite his unclear wording, had typified the name first.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
